1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:44,160 --> 00:01:47,460
Amazing...!

3
00:01:47,460 --> 00:01:49,370
Vito, what are you doing?

4
00:01:49,370 --> 00:01:51,140
Father, it's amazing!

5
00:01:51,140 --> 00:01:55,670
The president of the WEN
and Germa's boss are talking-rero !

6
00:01:55,670 --> 00:02:00,050
Of course, they talk.
They both have ears and mouths.

7
00:02:00,050 --> 00:02:04,680
Still, what a party-rero !

8
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:08,190
Eldest son and minister of candy: Perospero.

9
00:02:08,190 --> 00:02:11,650
Eldest daughter and the minister of fruit: Compote.

10
00:02:12,210 --> 00:02:15,070
Second son: Sweet Commander Katakuri.

11
00:02:15,070 --> 00:02:18,530
Fourteenth daughter: Sweet Commander Smoothie.

12
00:02:18,530 --> 00:02:21,950
Third son: Daifuku.
Fourth son: Oven.

13
00:02:21,950 --> 00:02:25,870
Countless monsters are gathered here...

14
00:02:25,870 --> 00:02:29,920
It was reassuring to have them as allies,

15
00:02:32,350 --> 00:02:36,680
so it's crazy to think that they'll be our enemies soon-rero.

16
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:38,090
Huh? "Enemies"?

17
00:02:38,090 --> 00:02:41,280
If you have time to worry,
go check downstairs!

18
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:44,220
Okay, Father. Let's go, Gotti.

19
00:02:44,220 --> 00:02:47,470
I heard that the wedding cake
will be very fancy.

20
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:08,960
Mama.

21
00:03:10,940 --> 00:03:13,460
Here is Mother Carmel.

22
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:19,300
Yes... My beloved...

23
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:21,020
Mother!

24
00:03:21,020 --> 00:03:26,190
Oh, it's always nice to see her smiling brightly.

25
00:03:26,190 --> 00:03:27,890
She's like the sun.

26
00:03:31,630 --> 00:03:36,070
That's right.
Mother is the light of this world!

27
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:39,900
No one knows who she is, though...

28
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:44,280
This is my first tea party,
so I am not familiar...

29
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:48,370
How are you related to this lady, Big Mom?

30
00:03:49,370 --> 00:03:51,960
You should really...

31
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:54,670
mind your own business!

32
00:04:00,340 --> 00:04:03,340
Cheers!

33
00:04:05,810 --> 00:04:07,570
How's everything going down there?

34
00:04:07,570 --> 00:04:12,350
The cooks finished preparing for the tea party,
so they're enjoying a banquet.

35
00:04:12,350 --> 00:04:16,020
We blocked all passages in the meantime.

36
00:04:16,020 --> 00:04:20,270
Good. With that done, nobody will
be able to come up here for a while.

37
00:04:20,280 --> 00:04:26,950
Now we'll set the horned transponder snails
to jam radio signals and isolate the venue.

38
00:04:26,950 --> 00:04:29,290
Don't forget to set up
for "you-know-what," too.

39
00:04:29,290 --> 00:04:30,620
Yes, sir.

40
00:04:33,410 --> 00:04:39,700
In honor of your daughter's wedding,
we brought you a present, Charlotte.

41
00:04:39,710 --> 00:04:43,120
Oh, a treasure chest!

42
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:45,370
My favorite!

43
00:04:45,370 --> 00:04:47,930
I wonder what's inside.

44
00:04:47,930 --> 00:04:51,310
I, too, brought you a present, Linlin.

45
00:04:51,310 --> 00:04:53,640
Take one from me too!

46
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:57,270
Mine's something rare from the south.

47
00:04:57,270 --> 00:05:01,150
Well, mine is from the farthest reaches of the north.

48
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:06,990
I'm so grateful!
 It's always a pleasure to get so many presents!

49
00:05:06,990 --> 00:05:09,940
Thank you!

50
00:05:09,940 --> 00:05:12,160
I'm so happy!

51
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:18,330
Speaking of treasure chests, Mamigo,
I heard you've obtained a great undersea treasure.

52
00:05:18,330 --> 00:05:19,620
Oh?

53
00:05:19,630 --> 00:05:24,040
Word reached you quickly.
That's my Morgans!

54
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:25,380
It's true.

55
00:05:26,130 --> 00:05:31,390
I now possess a chest that has been an heirloom
for generations of undersea royalty!

56
00:05:32,630 --> 00:05:37,980
Neptune actually let it slip from his grasp.

57
00:05:41,490 --> 00:05:45,280
The legendary...

58
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:47,910
Tamate Box!

59
00:05:49,710 --> 00:05:52,480
Oh! Look how fancy it is!

60
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:54,040
What's in it?

61
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:57,000
Have you opened it yet, Mamigo?!

62
00:05:57,000 --> 00:06:01,240
I'm saving it for the feast after Pudding's wedding,

63
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:07,260
I'll open all the presents
for everyone to see!

64
00:06:12,100 --> 00:06:13,350
Father!

65
00:06:13,350 --> 00:06:15,630
Oh, you all done?

66
00:06:15,630 --> 00:06:18,140
Everything is ready-rero.

67
00:06:18,140 --> 00:06:20,230
Okay. Good job.

68
00:06:20,230 --> 00:06:22,690
Guys, go get changed.

69
00:06:22,690 --> 00:06:23,610
Yes, sir.

70
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:28,650
Caesar, bring out the mirror.

71
00:06:28,650 --> 00:06:30,830
You jerk! Don't call me that!

72
00:06:32,640 --> 00:06:35,220
So this is the entrance to the tea party.

73
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:41,080
Enjoy it while you can, scumbags!

74
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:43,470
Caesar Clown?

75
00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:45,700
You're scum too.

76
00:06:45,700 --> 00:06:48,760
Just hide that mirror somewhere already.

77
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:50,640
Shut up! I know what I'm doing!

78
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:53,260
When Big Mom starts shrieking,

79
00:06:53,260 --> 00:06:58,090
you gotta bring that mirror and fly into the hall.
Just do your job.

80
00:06:59,230 --> 00:07:02,520
That's our only escape route.

81
00:07:02,520 --> 00:07:05,940
So be sure to not get any ideas.

82
00:07:05,940 --> 00:07:08,330
It's too late for me to betray you!

83
00:07:08,330 --> 00:07:11,570
This is bad!
Bege and his crew are up to something!

84
00:07:19,850 --> 00:07:21,660
I carved it off.

85
00:07:21,660 --> 00:07:25,710
Information leaks will bring unexpected crises.

86
00:07:25,710 --> 00:07:28,630
The ceremony starts in 30 minutes.

87
00:07:28,630 --> 00:07:34,110
Are Straw Hat and his crew ready?
He better not be fooling around again...

88
00:07:34,110 --> 00:07:38,350
Check for yourself!
They're in your body!

89
00:07:46,370 --> 00:07:49,600
Hey, you fools! Why're you sleeping?!

90
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:51,320
You should be getting ready!

91
00:07:51,900 --> 00:07:53,700
Let them sleep.

92
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:57,320
They haven't had time to rest
since they arrived.

93
00:07:57,320 --> 00:07:59,660
I'll wake them up 10 minutes before.

94
00:07:59,660 --> 00:08:01,490
I can't believe this.

95
00:08:01,490 --> 00:08:04,790
If they become a burden,
I'll abandon them immediately.

96
00:08:04,790 --> 00:08:06,540
Don't worry.

97
00:08:07,690 --> 00:08:11,670
I'll get everything ready for them.

98
00:08:14,970 --> 00:08:17,820
Those idiots... How ridiculous.

99
00:08:17,820 --> 00:08:18,600
Right!

100
00:08:20,140 --> 00:08:22,480
You need to go back inside.

101
00:08:23,230 --> 00:08:26,090
I'm gonna go into the hall.

102
00:08:26,090 --> 00:08:28,770
Everyone, prepare yourselves!

103
00:08:30,490 --> 00:08:32,700
Once we enter,

104
00:08:34,740 --> 00:08:37,020
there's no turning back!

105
00:08:39,540 --> 00:08:42,450
I hope you're ready too...

106
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:46,080
Vinsmoke Sanji!

107
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:55,500
I...

108
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:58,730
I wasn't planning on getting married
when I came here so...

109
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:04,600
it's really surreal for me
to see you like this...

110
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:07,410
I feel like I'm dreaming...

111
00:09:08,190 --> 00:09:10,490
Stay cool, stay cool.

112
00:09:10,490 --> 00:09:12,570
I won't be fooled again.

113
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:21,620
Is it...

114
00:09:23,190 --> 00:09:26,960
a good dream or a bad dream?

115
00:09:27,820 --> 00:09:30,540
Oh man, she's so cute!

116
00:09:30,540 --> 00:09:33,770
Of... O-O-Of course, it's a good dream!

117
00:09:33,770 --> 00:09:36,880
Really?! That's a relief!

118
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:38,720
Hey, calm down!

119
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:41,510
She's just acting!

120
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:43,980
She's planning to kill you!

121
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:50,150
Oh?

122
00:09:50,150 --> 00:09:54,030
Unless, I really was just dreaming...

123
00:09:54,030 --> 00:09:58,290
No, no, no! Don't be fooled!
You know the truth!

124
00:09:58,290 --> 00:10:01,060
Sanji-san, is there something wrong?

125
00:10:01,060 --> 00:10:04,980
What? N-No, no, no, no! It's just...

126
00:10:06,540 --> 00:10:07,570
That's right!

127
00:10:08,580 --> 00:10:12,440
A-About the wedding kiss... Um...

128
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:17,100
I was thinking that If you're embarrassed...
doing it in front of all those people...

129
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:20,220
I-I-I could maybe kiss you
 on the forehead instead...

130
00:10:22,210 --> 00:10:25,890
It's okay to kiss me on the lips.
We're gonna be husband and wife.

131
00:10:42,190 --> 00:10:43,680
What was that noise?!

132
00:10:44,510 --> 00:10:47,040
Prince Sanji crashed into the ceiling?!

133
00:10:48,540 --> 00:10:50,750
How did that happen?

134
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:52,710
He's bleeding so much!

135
00:10:52,710 --> 00:10:54,000
Oh, no!

136
00:10:55,210 --> 00:10:56,860
Sanji-san !

137
00:10:57,590 --> 00:11:00,800
What's wrong with this perverted imp?!

138
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:02,820
I can't wait to blow him away!

139
00:11:41,470 --> 00:11:43,300
Is everything all right?

140
00:11:43,300 --> 00:11:46,220
Yeah... It's all going well.

141
00:11:46,220 --> 00:11:51,440
That's good.
This is a very special day for us.

142
00:11:52,210 --> 00:11:54,900
Don't drop your guard. Lick.

143
00:11:55,690 --> 00:11:57,190
I know.

144
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:03,660
It's 12 o'clock! It's 12 o'clock!

145
00:12:27,430 --> 00:12:33,270
Ladies and gentlemen!
It's time for today's main event!

146
00:12:33,270 --> 00:12:38,230
The 35th daughter of the Charlotte family,
Madam Charlotte Pudding,

147
00:12:38,230 --> 00:12:42,610
and the third son of Vinsmoke family,
Prince Vinsmoke Sanji...

148
00:12:42,610 --> 00:12:44,820
Their royal wedding...

149
00:12:44,820 --> 00:12:47,330
starts now!

150
00:12:51,830 --> 00:12:53,120
♪ Marriage! ♪

151
00:12:53,120 --> 00:12:55,620
♪ Marriage! ♪

152
00:12:55,620 --> 00:12:58,000
♪ Marriage! ♪

153
00:13:10,060 --> 00:13:11,810
♪ Marriage! Marriage! ♪

154
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:15,810
That's awesome!

155
00:13:16,690 --> 00:13:21,480
Without further ado,
here are the bride and groom!

156
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:33,120
Wow!

157
00:13:39,710 --> 00:13:42,880
Emperor Big Mom and her pirates

158
00:13:42,880 --> 00:13:47,640
and the evil army Germa 66:

159
00:13:48,340 --> 00:13:53,680
This young couple will unite
their notorious families!

160
00:13:55,270 --> 00:13:58,200
Mariage de raison !

161
00:13:55,270 --> 00:13:58,200
French - "marriage of convenience"

162
00:14:01,190 --> 00:14:08,700
When these two tie the knot,
 it will be the start of a fearsome new era!

163
00:14:08,700 --> 00:14:11,260
Give it up for them!

164
00:14:14,660 --> 00:14:15,830
Look at that!

165
00:14:17,290 --> 00:14:20,210
For this extremely beautiful day!

166
00:14:24,130 --> 00:14:26,510
Give it up!

167
00:14:32,810 --> 00:14:34,140
Unbelievable!

168
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:38,020
What a great actor!

169
00:14:40,730 --> 00:14:44,230
The bloody wedding has begun!

170
00:14:52,410 --> 00:14:53,990
Luffy!

171
00:15:00,460 --> 00:15:04,340
The ceremony has begun! Luffy!

172
00:15:04,340 --> 00:15:07,680
I'm still hungry...

173
00:15:08,420 --> 00:15:10,260
Wake up!

174
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:13,680
Do you wanna let Sanji down?!

175
00:15:21,690 --> 00:15:24,770
Hey! Is there any way to wake him up?!

176
00:15:24,770 --> 00:15:28,370
He was running around the forest
right before he fell asleep so...

177
00:15:28,370 --> 00:15:31,110
Food is the only thing that'll wake him up.

178
00:15:31,110 --> 00:15:34,280
Hey, do you have any meat?!
We don't have time!

179
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:37,080
– Meat?
– He's gonna have breakfast now?

180
00:15:59,460 --> 00:16:02,420
This is your requiem!

181
00:16:02,420 --> 00:16:06,570
Just listen to it with that
stupid look on your face, Sanji!

182
00:16:19,830 --> 00:16:22,080
Thank you, Sanji-san !

183
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:24,560
Sanji-san, I'm...

184
00:16:25,660 --> 00:16:27,790
so happy!

185
00:16:27,790 --> 00:16:32,260
P... P-P-P-P-Pudding-chan...

186
00:16:32,260 --> 00:16:35,970
Me... Me too!

187
00:16:40,760 --> 00:16:44,180
No! No! Stay rational!

188
00:16:44,180 --> 00:16:47,980
If you're not careful, you'll...

189
00:16:47,990 --> 00:16:50,230
you'll get killed!

190
00:16:52,150 --> 00:16:53,280
♪ Marriage! ♪

191
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:54,320
♪ Marriage! ♪

192
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:55,280
♪ Marriage! ♪

193
00:16:55,280 --> 00:16:56,320
♪ Marriage! ♪

194
00:16:56,320 --> 00:17:00,200
♪ Marriage! ♪

195
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:02,870
♪ Tough love... ♪

196
00:17:02,870 --> 00:17:04,250
♪ I've been there... ♪

197
00:17:04,250 --> 00:17:06,760
♪ Bitter love... ♪

198
00:17:06,760 --> 00:17:08,220
♪ I've been there... ♪

199
00:17:08,220 --> 00:17:14,010
♪ Yet despite it all, when it's true love... ♪

200
00:17:14,010 --> 00:17:18,300
♪ I must reach the aisle ♪

201
00:17:18,300 --> 00:17:22,100
♪ Even if I were drenched with rain ♪

202
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:25,850
♪ Even if spears rain down on me ♪

203
00:17:25,850 --> 00:17:30,870
♪ Never let that hand go! ♪

204
00:17:30,870 --> 00:17:32,780
– Head Chef!
 – Head Chef!

205
00:17:32,780 --> 00:17:34,240
Head Chef!

206
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:40,780
♪ It's time to unveil the... ♪

207
00:17:40,780 --> 00:17:47,870
♪ wedding cake! ♪

208
00:18:43,760 --> 00:18:45,280
Bravo!

209
00:18:45,810 --> 00:18:48,090
Beautiful! Brilliant!

210
00:18:48,090 --> 00:18:50,920
It's so big and fancy!

211
00:18:50,920 --> 00:18:52,860
Looks delicious!

212
00:18:52,860 --> 00:18:55,570
What a magnificent wedding cake!

213
00:18:55,570 --> 00:19:00,670
You did a wonderful job, Streusen!
I have to give you praise!

214
00:19:00,670 --> 00:19:02,620
It's more than I deserve!

215
00:19:02,620 --> 00:19:06,950
I can't wait to eat it!

216
00:19:15,710 --> 00:19:20,380
How lovely! Our altar is on top of the sweet cake!

217
00:19:20,380 --> 00:19:23,180
You are what's lovely!

218
00:19:23,180 --> 00:19:27,690
Oh, stop! Come on, Sanji-san !

219
00:19:27,690 --> 00:19:29,560
Just drop dead already!

220
00:19:29,560 --> 00:19:34,340
Pudding-chan looks so beautiful...
It feels like I'm watching my younger self.

221
00:19:34,340 --> 00:19:36,740
How many decades ago?

222
00:19:36,740 --> 00:19:38,330
You must have a death wish.

223
00:19:39,320 --> 00:19:40,710
Ouch!

224
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:48,790
Enjoy it while you can, my guests.

225
00:19:48,790 --> 00:19:52,920
The climax is approaching...

226
00:20:05,860 --> 00:20:08,720
It'll all be over before you know it...

227
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:12,310
Please. Enjoy the ceremony
from these VIP seats.

228
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:18,400
It's about to start!

229
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:20,280
The bloodbath!

230
00:20:21,040 --> 00:20:23,950
At the moment of the wedding kiss...

231
00:20:23,950 --> 00:20:26,870
...the bloody banquet will begin.

232
00:20:26,870 --> 00:20:32,110
I'm sorry! But you Vinsmokes are in my way!

233
00:20:35,310 --> 00:20:38,060
Sanji's lucky!

234
00:20:38,060 --> 00:20:41,740
If I'd known she was that pretty,
I wouldn't have minded marrying her.

235
00:20:41,740 --> 00:20:44,650
Marrying Big Mom's daughter? Idiot.

236
00:20:44,650 --> 00:20:48,040
He's a sacrifice. Don't forget.

237
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:51,860
Once he's married,
he'll be under Big Mom's control forever.

238
00:20:51,860 --> 00:20:55,060
You're right.
It wouldn't be worth it.

239
00:20:56,080 --> 00:21:01,080
I see... We're surrounded
by the Charlotte siblings.

240
00:21:01,670 --> 00:21:04,360
We have nowhere to run.

241
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:08,330
And we're unarmed,
so we're basically sitting ducks.

242
00:21:08,920 --> 00:21:10,340
That's how it should be...

243
00:21:11,430 --> 00:21:14,380
Germa is a kingdom that shouldn't exist.

244
00:21:15,100 --> 00:21:16,290
But...

245
00:21:16,840 --> 00:21:17,720
Sanji...

246
00:21:22,170 --> 00:21:24,420
I want you to get away.

247
00:21:25,190 --> 00:21:28,190
You have a plan, right?
Can I trust you?

248
00:21:29,180 --> 00:21:30,220
Luffy-kun !

249
00:21:30,220 --> 00:21:34,060
In sickness and in health,

250
00:21:34,060 --> 00:21:37,300
for richer, for poorer,

251
00:21:37,300 --> 00:21:38,980
to have and to hold,

252
00:21:38,980 --> 00:21:42,730
till death do you part...

253
00:21:43,320 --> 00:21:46,530
Hurry up, guys! We don't have time!

254
00:21:46,540 --> 00:21:49,740
You don't get to tell us that!

255
00:21:50,640 --> 00:21:54,780
Do you pledge yourself to love
and to be loyal to each other?

256
00:22:00,380 --> 00:22:03,840
My wish is finally coming true!

257
00:22:16,100 --> 00:22:20,690
What's wrong, Pudding?
Why are you going to collapse?!

258
00:22:20,690 --> 00:22:24,900
Then, you may lift the veil and kiss the bride.

259
00:22:24,900 --> 00:22:26,780
Is something wrong, Brother?

260
00:22:27,710 --> 00:22:30,530
You saw the future, Katakuri!

261
00:22:36,160 --> 00:22:38,330
I'll lift your veil.

262
00:22:39,820 --> 00:22:40,880
Okay.

263
00:23:23,800 --> 00:23:26,340
Sanji, take a good look...

264
00:23:27,340 --> 00:23:28,380
at...

265
00:23:29,360 --> 00:23:31,660
at my creepy...

266
00:23:31,660 --> 00:23:33,880
third eye!

267
00:23:44,610 --> 00:23:45,960
Good boy.

268
00:23:47,050 --> 00:23:48,780
Stay like that...

269
00:23:52,040 --> 00:23:55,120
What a beautiful eye!

270
00:24:21,810 --> 00:24:23,230
What?

271
00:24:26,310 --> 00:24:30,690
I'm sorry! When I saw it up close,
I couldn't help it...

272
00:24:31,870 --> 00:24:33,150
What is she doing?!

273
00:24:33,700 --> 00:24:35,620
Don't hesitate, Pudding!

274
00:24:36,460 --> 00:24:38,220
Pudding... -chan ?

275
00:24:40,040 --> 00:24:43,500
What is he saying?

276
00:24:43,500 --> 00:24:49,300
Everyone will be watching the groom, Sanji...

277
00:24:49,300 --> 00:24:54,180
He'll see your 
third eye for the first time!

278
00:24:54,980 --> 00:25:01,770
In that moment, he'll see his beautiful bride's creepy face,

279
00:25:01,770 --> 00:25:03,730
and he'll be distracted for a moment!

280
00:25:16,120 --> 00:25:18,240
Screw him!

281
00:25:19,120 --> 00:25:21,160
What is he thinking?!

282
00:25:21,790 --> 00:25:26,980
Ever since I was born, I've never been told...!

283
00:25:26,980 --> 00:25:32,460
Not a single person has ever told me
that this eye is beautiful!

284
00:25:32,460 --> 00:25:35,760
What's wrong, Pudding?!
Just shoot him!

285
00:25:37,730 --> 00:25:40,400
No one's ever...

286
00:25:43,750 --> 00:25:46,770
Even if you're my daughter, I can't deny
that's creepy...

287
00:25:46,770 --> 00:25:48,950
Grow out your bangs, Pudding.

288
00:25:51,340 --> 00:25:54,080
Yes... I understand, ma'am...

289
00:25:55,530 --> 00:25:57,490
She's a monster!

290
00:25:58,340 --> 00:26:00,630
So creepy!

291
00:26:00,630 --> 00:26:02,330
What's wrong with this kid?!

292
00:26:04,040 --> 00:26:06,710
Look! She's a freak!

293
00:26:08,350 --> 00:26:10,400
Don't do it!

294
00:26:16,630 --> 00:26:18,720
How's that, freak?!

295
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:20,930
Freak! Freak!

296
00:26:27,350 --> 00:26:30,560
I'm not gonna let you make fun of me!

297
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:33,960
You stupid trash...

298
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:35,860
I'll wipe you all out!

299
00:26:35,860 --> 00:26:38,360
Run!

300
00:26:48,530 --> 00:26:49,710
Pudding-chan...

301
00:26:51,350 --> 00:26:52,670
Screw you!

302
00:26:53,380 --> 00:26:56,980
I'm gonna kill you!

303
00:26:56,980 --> 00:27:00,510
I'm an ugly freak!

304
00:27:01,590 --> 00:27:04,650
Hey, did you forget the plan, Pudding?!

305
00:27:05,570 --> 00:27:07,480
Pudding-chan, are you okay?

306
00:27:09,520 --> 00:27:11,730
You do it, priest!

307
00:27:16,900 --> 00:27:18,950
That's no good! He'll miss!

308
00:27:33,380 --> 00:27:34,710
He dodged!

309
00:27:39,050 --> 00:27:41,180
Straw Hat! Now's the time!

310
00:27:41,180 --> 00:27:43,680
That's the gunshot, Luffy!

311
00:27:43,680 --> 00:27:45,510
Great! We'll make it!

312
00:27:47,890 --> 00:27:49,930
What was that gunshot?!

313
00:27:49,930 --> 00:27:51,430
The priest fired!

314
00:27:51,430 --> 00:27:52,930
No, he got shot!

315
00:27:52,930 --> 00:27:53,730
Why?!

316
00:27:53,730 --> 00:27:55,480
What's going on?!

317
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:56,610
Is this...?!

318
00:27:58,150 --> 00:28:03,050
What the hell is going on?!
Katakuri, what happened to Pudding?!

319
00:28:03,050 --> 00:28:07,290
We have a bigger problem!
It's an unanticipated situation, Mama!

320
00:28:07,290 --> 00:28:09,580
Not even I can do anything!

321
00:28:09,580 --> 00:28:12,580
What should we do?!
Sanji hasn't been shot!

322
00:28:12,580 --> 00:28:14,830
Is the plan still on?

323
00:28:14,830 --> 00:28:17,630
Let's go!

324
00:28:17,630 --> 00:28:22,510
I'm sorry, Mama!
I had no choice but to do what they told me to!

325
00:28:22,510 --> 00:28:25,390
We'll take Sanji back!

326
00:28:30,240 --> 00:28:31,520
What the...?!

327
00:28:32,220 --> 00:28:33,600
I can't stop them!

328
00:28:34,620 --> 00:28:37,400
They'll come out of there!

329
00:28:37,400 --> 00:28:38,650
What?!

330
00:28:57,590 --> 00:29:00,810
Big Mom!

